1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:05,595
Somewhere high in the stands, an old piper has played at every Scotland World Cup since nineteen seventy-four.

2
00:00:05,645 --> 00:00:10,440
He has never once played a song of celebration.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,570
Tonight, he is praying that changes.

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,995
Last time, we predicted Switzerland would edge Qatar one-nil.

5
00:00:21,045 --> 00:00:25,540
Tonight — two of football's bravest underdogs, fighting just to survive.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,060
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode ten. Haiti versus Scotland.

7
00:00:30,110 --> 00:00:33,170
The battle of the nearly-men.

8
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:42,880
And stay with me — because the final whistle of this one... makes BOTH teams dance.

9
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,377
First, the curse.

10
00:00:49,427 --> 00:00:52,303
Scotland has qualified for the World Cup more times than any nation on Earth...

11
00:00:52,353 --> 00:00:55,230
without EVER reaching the knockout stage.

12
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,443
Nineteen seventy-four: unbeaten, and still eliminated.

13
00:01:00,493 --> 00:01:03,937
Nineteen seventy-eight: one of the greatest goals ever scored...

14
00:01:03,987 --> 00:01:07,430
and they went home anyway.

15
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:11,625
Fifty years of the bravest heartbreak in football.

16
00:01:11,675 --> 00:01:14,800
And the old piper has played through every single tear.

17
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:21,975
Haiti's pain is quieter, but just as deep. One World Cup in nineteen seventy-four.

18
00:01:22,025 --> 00:01:25,500
Then a fifty-two-year silence.

19
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:32,925
Tonight, both nations need a win to survive. Two underdogs.

20
00:01:32,975 --> 00:01:36,400
One ticket out of the group. Everything on the line.

21
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,950
And nobody fights like a team with nothing but pride to lose.

22
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:47,505
Meet the Tartan heart.

23
00:01:47,555 --> 00:01:50,560
Scotland — fury, running, and fifty years of unfinished business.

24
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,547
Scott McTominay, the Serie A Player of the Year, who left a Manchester bench to conquer Italy.

25
00:01:55,597 --> 00:02:00,143
John McGinn, all craft and chaos.

26
00:02:00,193 --> 00:02:04,740
And Andy Robertson, the captain who never, ever stops running.

27
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,510
Heart. Fury. And a nation that refuses to quit.

28
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,125
But Haiti did not cross an ocean to bow.

29
00:02:17,175 --> 00:02:20,300
The Caribbean's unbreakable team plays for eleven million dreaming hearts.

30
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:31,050
Duckens Nazon, the striker who stacked supermarket shelves before football saved him — playing like this is his only World Cup.

31
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:37,395
Derrick Etienne Junior pulls the strings — he chose Haiti when America was calling.

32
00:02:37,445 --> 00:02:41,340
This team is pure, fearless defiance.

33
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,690
Two nations who know this might be their only night.

34
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,585
And the duel inside the match: McTominay against Nazon. Italy's best...

35
00:02:54,635 --> 00:02:59,720
against the man from the supermarket. Pure heart against pure hunger.

36
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:03,675
Our prediction — built on fifty years of Scottish pain and Haitian defiance.

37
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:06,900
Watch closely.

38
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,135
Seventeenth minute. Robertson's cross — McTominay, near post — header — GOAL!

39
00:03:12,185 --> 00:03:15,820
Scotland leads! The Tartan Army erupts!

40
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,865
But Haiti does not fold. Nazon fights for everything.

41
00:03:20,915 --> 00:03:23,880
And the clock ticks past the hour...

42
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,633
Sixty-third minute. A long ball.

43
00:03:30,683 --> 00:03:34,317
Nazon holds off his man, turns, shoots — a deflection — it loops up...

44
00:03:34,367 --> 00:03:38,000
and over the keeper!

45
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:41,140
ONE—ONE! The supermarket striker again!

46
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,830
An entire Caribbean nation explodes into dance!

47
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,335
Eighty-ninth minute — Shankland turns and shoots — OFF THE POST!

48
00:03:48,385 --> 00:03:51,720
Inches from breaking Scottish hearts again.

49
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,750
Full time in our story: one-one. And the cruelest twist — BOTH teams are eliminated.

50
00:03:56,800 --> 00:04:00,550
And yet... nobody leaves.

51
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:07,135
Do you agree? Comment TARTAN if Scotland finally break the curse one day.

52
00:04:07,185 --> 00:04:10,820
Comment HAITI if the Caribbean dream lives on.

53
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,480
And the old piper? Legend number ten: the Lone Piper.

54
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:22,510
Fifty years of heartbreak, and tonight... he finally plays a song of joy.

55
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,930
Because some battles are won just by showing up to fight.

56
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:31,410
Collect him inside the game.

57
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,577
Which brings us to YOU.

58
00:04:35,627 --> 00:04:38,703
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

59
00:04:38,753 --> 00:04:41,830
scores for you.

60
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:47,450
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple.

61
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,610
Hit like — send this to the friend whose team never gives up.

62
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:57,070
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

